name: DosageMinimumGapBetweenDose
title: Dosage - Minimum Gap Between Doses
description: The minimum amount of time that must pass between administering the specified dose amount.

element.short: Time that must pass between doses
element.definition: The minimum amount of time that must pass between administering the specified dose amount.
element.comment: Used on orders with flexible timing, such as PRN medications or PCA devices when there is a need to prevent too much medication from being administered in too short a period of time.
